Male: dorsal surface shiny. Claws of fore tarsi broadened, strongly hooked. Median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view (
Figure 2H
) more intensively tapering in distal half, apical part longer than in nominotypical subspecies, distinctly turned to right, apex very acute.
